    "created_at": "2012-01-20T01:54:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-20T01:54:50Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@takluyver's point is principally that there should be _one_ release of IPython that will work on 3.1, and that currently doesn't exist.  I agree with @fperez that we should not consider 3.1 an officially supported version going forward, but it might be nice to have that one release we can point to that is basically functional.  I would even be fine with an offshoot tag from current master or 0.12 with this patch applied, just so that we have a url for it.\n"
