    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Since even our own 3.x champion, @takluyver, doesn't have 3.1, then I really think we shouldn't bend over backwards for it.  Really: what's the value of having something that works for 3.1? Is _anyone_ using 3.1 and not 3.2 that we should worry about?\n\nI don't like putting it in a branch because then we have to keep it in our main repo forever.\n\nHow about we simply make a static upload of the sources for 0.12 with this patch applied and put them in a special subdir in archive.ipython.org?\n"
