    "updated_at": "2012-01-20T02:41:59Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'd be OK with that, though I'd prefer if @takluyver or someone with more experience using 2to3 than me does it.  I've only installed ipython on python3 for the first time this week, so I'm not really too familiar with how the 2to3 machinery operates; best if this is done by someone who knows the tools well.  @takluyver, if you're up for it, I'd suggest uploading it to a subdir of http://archive.ipython.org/release/0.12/, along with a simple README that explains the issue.  We can put an entry in the FAQ about it, I guess, so people find it more easily.\n\nIn that case it seems we can close this one, right?  Since we'll do it statically, there's no need to merge anything per se into master.   Closing now, we can always reopen if there's a change of idea.\n"
