    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm not quite sure of the best way to do it. `sdist` won't run 2to3, `bdist` will, but will produce a package that specifies it's for 3.2, and I don't know if just changing the filename would make things work. If I run 2to3 manually, I'd need to edit `setup.py` to avoid running it again. Either way, I'm going to need to have 3.1 to test.\n\nSomeone's helpfully got a [PPA](https://launchpad.net/~fkrull/+archive/deadsnakes), so I'll download 3.1 this evening and have a look. I doubt that it actually gets all of these wrong, or someone would have noticed the bug long ago.\n"
