    "created_at": "2012-01-20T20:02:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-20T20:02:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Well, if it's actually real work, my vote is on not doing this, period.  We can leave a link to this PR so that if anyone _really_ needs it, they can do it themselves.\n\nOur time is valuable and limited, and I'd much rather Thomas use his precious resources on new code and PRs than on solving a problem for which I'm not even sure there's an audience at all.  Users who have jumped on python3 but can't update to 3.2, if they exist, may have to do this for themselves manually: we can help them by pointing them to [the patch for this PR](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/1259.patch), but we're not obligated to burn our cycles in doing all of it, when that would mean not doing other more relevant/important new work.\n\nI won't say more on this, and if anyone does want to make it happen, it's of course their prerogative.  But as far as I'm concerned, a simple entry in the FAQ pointing to the patch is sufficient.\n"
  },
